Eskom will start stage 2 load-shedding from 09:00 today, and it will run until 22:00. Eskom said this was the result of a shortage of capacity, and it once again apologised for the shortage. Load-shedding is a daily fact for South Africans of late, and people have to plan their work and personal lives around the associated schedules. There have also been reports that load-shedding is here to stay for several years to come. The tweet below details the latest load-shedding notice. 